WS2 film crystallinity and strain with respect to sputtering powers.

The optical behavior of the as-deposited WS2 thin films at different RF powers was characterized by UV-VIS spectrometry. The absorbance of as-deposited films was calculated by the Beer–Lambert law, and the optical properties of the WS2 film are shown in Fig. 8. The Beer–Lambert law (or Beer’s law) is the linear relationship between the absorbance and concentration of an absorbing species. The general Beer–Lambert law is usually written as follows40:3A=a(λ)∗b∗c\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
